TITLE: Writing an indexing function for blockchain events
DESCRIPTION: Implementing an indexing function that processes a contract event and writes data to the database. This example handles the Transfer event from the Blitmap contract.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ponder-sh/ponder/blob/main/docs/pages/docs/getting-started/new-project.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { ponder } from "ponder:registry";
import { blitmapTokens } from "ponder:schema";

ponder.on("Blitmap:Transfer", async ({ event, context }) => {
  await context.db.insert(blitmapTokens).values({
    id: event.args.tokenId,
    owner: event.args.to,
  });
});
```

