TITLE: Querying Ponder Indexing Status via HTTP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to retrieve the indexing status using a simple curl request to the /status endpoint, showing the status of multiple networks including block numbers and timestamps.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ponder-sh/ponder/blob/main/docs/pages/docs/advanced/status.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl http://localhost:42069/status
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "mainnet": {
    "ready": true,
    "block": {
      "number": 20293450,
      "timestamp": 1720823759
    }
  },
  "base": {
    "ready": true,
    "block": {
      "number": 17017206,
      "timestamp": 1720823759
    }
  }
}
```

